# Node.js PATH workaround (temporary)

Node.js is installed at `C:\Program Files\nodejs\node.exe` (v24.x) but is **not** on the system/user PATH yet. The user will apply a permanent PATH fix later when admin access is available.

**This is a known, recurring issue.** Do not suggest bare `shopify`, `node`, or `npm` commands without the workaround.

## For the user (terminal)

Prefer project scripts — they apply PATH automatically:

```powershell
.\scripts\theme-dev.ps1
```

## For the agent (every shell command)

**Always** prefix Node/Shopify commands with:

```powershell
$env:PATH += ";C:\Program Files\nodejs"
```

Or dot-source `scripts/_ensure-node.ps1` before running CLI tools.

Never assume `node`, `npm`, or `shopify` work in a fresh terminal without this.
